title.narrative: The health systems at national level and in select provinces are strengthened to accelerate equitable access to high impact interventions for reducing preventable newborn deaths, early childhood illnesses and disability

description.narrative: UNICEF supported UHC through the Common Framework of Health Systems Strengthening for Primary Health Care, maintaining focus on equity and the unfinished agenda to reduce child morbidity and mortality. UNICEF's comparative advantage was applied at three levels of the health system: community, local government and national. UNICEF supported the development of service delivery models with sustainable financing mechanisms targeting children with disabilities, and premature and small newborns. A government-led multisectoral coalition and city-led models to prevent child road traffic injuries were established. While responding to measles and polio outbreaks, UNICEF strengthened routine immunization program through evidence-based planning and monitoring. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:07/02/2020
